HB 4143-1
(LC 175)
2/9/26 (DFY/ps)
Requested by Representative CHOTZEN
PROPOSED AMENDMENTS TO
HOUSE BILL 4143
1 On page 1 of the printed bill, delete lines 11 through 13 and insert:
2 “(c) ‘Qualified payment’ means moneys that a state agency is obligated
3 to transfer to the federal government pursuant to contract or federal law,
4 but excluding:
5 “(A) Payroll taxes for officers or employees of state agencies;
6 “(B) Amounts voluntarily withheld from unemployment insurance and
7 paid family and medical leave insurance benefits for federal income tax
8 purposes; and
9 “(C) Any revenues collected or overpaid benefits recovered pursuant to
10 the Federal Unemployment Tax Act or ORS chapter 657.”.
11 On page 2, after line 17, insert:
12 “SECTION 3. (1) Sections 1 and 2 of this 2026 Act are repealed on
13 January 2, 2037.
14 “(2) Any moneys remaining in the Federal Moneys Holding Account
15 established under section 2 of this 2026 Act on the date specified in
16 subsection (1) of this section shall be transferred to the General Fund
17 to be used for general governmental purposes.”.
18 In line 18, delete “3” and insert “4”.
19

